-- Lincoln National Increases Buyback Authorization to $1 Billion
-- B y   Z a c h a r y   T r a c e r
-- 2012-08-09T12:19:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-09/lincoln-national-increases-buyback-authorization-to-1-billion.html
Lincoln National Corp. (LNC)  the insurer
that hired Ellen Cooper from Goldman Sachs Group Inc. as chief
investment officer, said it increased the size of its share
buyback authorization to $1 billion.  The quarterly dividend will remain 8 cents a share, the
Radnor, Pennsylvania-based insurer said today in a statement
distributed by PR Newswire.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Zachary Tracer in New York at 
 ztracer1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
